1. SUMMARY

   Realness is source-available. You may read it, run it, modify it, and stand
   up your own instance. Each instance has exactly one human moderator who takes
   responsibility for the content created within it. Anyone or any organization
   may self-host — and by doing so assumes full legal responsibility for the
   instance they operate. If your team or organization needs a formal license
   agreement — for procurement, legal compliance, or to support the project —
   we offer commercial tiers at https://realness.online/pricing. Source-available
   does not mean open-contribution: publishing the source creates no obligation
   on the author to review, accept, or maintain contributions.

2. DEFINITIONS

   "Software" — the Realness source code and assets in this repository.
   "Instance" — a deployed, running copy of the Software serving users.
   "Moderator" — the single human person responsible for an Instance.
   "Outputs" — works a user creates with the Software (e.g. posters, exports).
   "Personal Instance" — one Instance run by one human Moderator for themselves,
       their family, or a non-commercial personal circle.
   "Commercial Instance" — any Instance run by or for an organization, team,
       studio, company, or institution, or in connection with paid services.

3. GRANT — SOURCE & PERSONAL USE

   Subject to this license, you are granted a worldwide, royalty-free,
