   organization without a formal license is done entirely at your own risk
   and without the protections the commercial license provides.

5. RESPONSIBILITY

   Each Instance has exactly one Moderator. The Moderator — and, for a
   Commercial Instance, the operating organization — is solely responsible for:
     (a) the content created, stored, organized, or distributed on that
         Instance; and
     (b) the Instance's compliance with all applicable laws (including content,
         privacy, and consumer-protection law) in the jurisdictions it serves.
   The author of the Software is not a party to, and assumes no responsibility
   for, any Instance the author does not itself operate. Self-hosting transfers
   operational and legal responsibility for that Instance to the self-hoster.

